subSubSection.paragraph:
Male genitalia (
Fig. 12
). Median lobe of aedeagus shorter than parameres, apex acuminate. Parameres symmetrical, not articulated (as typical of the genus); wider at base, narrower towards apex; apex rounded. Base asymmetrical. Genital segment asymmetrical, strongly sclerotized; struts asymmetrical, with different length. Ventrite VIII U-shaped, with wide apical membranous lamina. Spiculum strongly bilobed.
